-- Hong Kong Stocks Rise Third Day on U.S. Data, Developers
-- B y   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a
-- 2013-05-20T01:46:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-20/hong-kong-stocks-rise-third-day-on-u-s-data-developers.html
Hong Kong  stocks  rose a third day,
with the city’s benchmark index heading for a three-month high,
after China developers gained on higher home prices and as U.S.
leading indicators and consumer sentiment data signaled
improvement in the world’s largest economy.  The Hang Seng Index rose 1.3 percent to 23,389.05 as of
9:35 a.m. All but one stock advanced on the 50-member gauge.
Markets in the city were closed on May 17 for a holiday. The
 Hang Seng China Enterprises Index (HSCEI)  of mainland companies rose 1.6
percent to 11,191.61.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kana Nishizawa in Hong Kong at 
